rComments: One of the most exciting profs. I took two courses with him: CIN101 in first year and CIN301 in second. Listening to his lectures and lsitening to him talking about movies is like listening to someone describing their most favorite thing in the world. Though readings he gives are long. Still, probably my favourite professor in this university.

Professor Stoddard is a classy, friendly, and composed professor. He be on his suit and tie. He is so cute and reminds me of a younger version of the old guy in the movie UP. Every lecture he delivers is quality and you can tell he has a strong passion for cinema. Take this course and explore beyond the surface level of the cinematic experience!
Easygoing prof and easy class. Getting a credit for watching movies why not :) I recommend to all students.
Best of the best. Bird course if you put the work in.
Prof. Stoddard's lectures are clear, engaging, and insightful. Great course.

Stoddard is probably the best professor I had in University. Not only does he understand and accommodate his students, he is a passionate lecturer, who knows what he's doing-- and he's doing it right. I had him in VCC309 as well, and he's just as great. His lectures are interesting, and he is very fair.

Professor Stoddard is a cool, classy, and passionate lecturer. He is extremely approachable. The lectures were always interesting and thought provoking. The TAs for this course were also extremely qualified and really want what's best for their students.   This course is a life changer. Be prepared to watch A LOT of movies.
